v2.0.1 | Mar 10 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] email alert system reimagined: HTML+text dual-format email alerts with
      unified rfxn design language (teal brand bar, card-based threat entries,
      color-coded hit types); new template engine using {{TOKEN}} placeholders
      via alert_lib's _alert_tpl_render(); lmd_alert.sh dedicated alert library
      with data preparation (_lmd_parse_hitlist, _lmd_set_global_vars,
      _lmd_set_entry_vars, _lmd_compute_summary), rendering pipeline
      (_lmd_render_text, _lmd_render_html), and messaging dispatch; scan,
      panel, and digest alert types all support HTML+text; SMTP relay support
      (smtp_relay, smtp_from, smtp_user, smtp_pass config vars); email_format
      config var (text/html/both); per-entry formatted Slack Block Kit, Telegram
      MarkdownV2, and Discord embed messaging templates replace trivial
      one-liners; legacy .etpl sourced-as-shell templates removed; custom
      template overrides via alert/custom.d/ preserved
[New] native batch scan engine: 43x faster end-to-end (1,217s to 28s on
      ~10,000 files); batch grep -F Aho-Corasick hex matching with parallel
      workers replaces per-file Perl hexfifo.pl/hexstring.pl; Perl dependency
      removed; batch parallel MD5 scanning reduces ~100,000 subprocess forks
      to ~10; ClamAV hex wildcard support (??, (aa|bb), *, nibble) for custom
      signatures; scan_workers controls worker count (default: auto);
      multi-pass pipeline (MD5, HEX, strlen, YARA) with unified progress;
      live scan progress with per-file throughput from workers (MD5 every
      500 files, HEX every 100 files) and elapsed timers for ClamAV/YARA;
      auto worker count changed to 2 per core (up to 8); progress
      suppressed in background mode for maximum throughput
[New] batch hit processing pipeline: replaces per-hit record_hit()+quarantine()
      fork loops with unified bulk operations across all scan engines (native
      MD5/HEX, ClamAV, YARA, string length); bulk stat+md5sum via xargs,
      single-pass awk for hits_history and scan_session generation, batched
      chattr/chmod/chown for quarantine; eliminates ~12-15 subprocess forks
      per hit; CLI quarantine (-q) also uses batch path when quarantine_clean
      is disabled
[New] native YARA scanning: scan_yara=1 enables YARA as an independent scan
      stage with yara or yr (YARA-X) binary; supports custom rules via
      custom.yara and custom.yara.d/ drop-in directory; scan_yara_scope
      controls rule overlap with ClamAV YARA; compiled rules via yarac;
      hookscan passes scan_yara for ModSecurity upload scanning;
      import_custsigs_yara_url for remote rule import; --scan-list batch
      scanning for YARA >= 4.0; issue #392, #277, #239
[New] shared alert_lib integration: all email, Slack, Telegram, and Discord
      alerting primitives replaced with calls to shared library
[New] Discord alerting support: discord_alert and discord_webhook_url config
      variables; scan reports uploaded via Discord webhook multipart upload
[New] shared elog_lib integration: structured event logging with dual
      app/audit log model; eout() replaced with thin elog() wrapper; audit
      trail in /var/log/maldet/audit.log (root only); inode-preserving log
      truncation; elog_event() calls at 11 operation points with graceful
      degradation
[New] shared tlog_lib integration: multi-mode incremental log tracking
      (bytes/lines), atomic cursor writes, flock-based cursor locking,
      compressed rotation support; replaces 9 subprocess forks with
      in-process tlog_read() calls
[New] shared pkg_lib integration: install.sh and uninstall.sh refactored to
      use shared packaging primitives (backup, copy, symlink, cron, service,
      platform detection); timestamped backup naming; project-root
      uninstall.sh for clean removal across all init systems and OS families;
      RPM/DEB packaging infrastructure in pkg/ directory
[New] cron.watchdog weekly watchdog script for independent fallback signature
      updates when primary cron.daily is broken or stale
[New] cron.daily: explicit cPanel addon/subdomain document root detection
      via /etc/userdatadomains; Bitrix panel detection; issue #268, #381
[New] BATS test suite with 27 test files and UAT acceptance suite (103+
      scenarios covering YARA, ClamAV, alerting, signatures, cron, and
      monitor); GitHub Actions CI with 9-target matrix

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] scan-time HTML email: move hits file into place before genalert renders
      template; dirty scans were showing "No Threats Detected" clean-scan
      celebration because _resolve_html_for_session() could not find the hits
      file (mv happened after genalert, not before)
[Fix] messaging dispatch: pass scan report as attachment to Slack file
      upload and Telegram sendDocument; capture handler stderr for diagnostic
      logging (API errors, curl failures now visible in event_log)
[Fix] Slack alerting: migrate from deprecated files.upload API to
      files.getUploadURLExternal + files.completeUploadExternal; fix
      multi-channel support; check curl exit codes and API responses;
      issue #458
[Fix] Telegram alerting: add missing /bot prefix before token in Bot API
      URL causing all alerts to fail; hide bot token from /proc/PID/cmdline
      using curl -K config file; check sendDocument exit code; issue #461
[Fix] Slack and Telegram alerts now fire in monitor mode digest/daily
      reports, not just single-file scan alerts; issue #387
[Fix] panel alerts: include signature name; fix hit parsing for paths with
      spaces; fix temp file cleanup leak; restrict messaging dispatch to
      file and digest alert types only; InterWorx empty master_domain guard;
      issue #426
[Fix] import_conf() remote config sourcing replaced with safe parser
      preventing remote code execution; config source order corrected to
      match documented loading order
[Fix] -co/--config-option: reject command substitution, semicolons, pipes,
      and shell metacharacters in config values
[Fix] hookscan.sh: validate filenames from ModSecurity inspectFile; reject
      shell metacharacters, non-printable characters, and non-existent files;
      replace hardcoded paths with variables
[Fix] file permissions hardened: conf.maldet 0644 to 0640; sigdir, logdir,
      tmpdir from 755 to 750; custom signature files restricted to 640/750
      when pubscan disabled
[Fix] --user flag validates username (empty, path traversal, non-existent);
      restore() validates .info file paths against traversal
[Fix] JSON injection in ELK and Slack payloads via _json_escape() helper;
      strip CR/LF from email subjects to prevent header injection
[Fix] monitor_check(): remove double ClamAV scan; clamd fatal errors no
      longer cause false quarantines; fix YARA filtering in both engine
      branches; issue #454, #447, #459
[Fix] monitor_kill() and monitor_cycle(): guard empty PID; reload sources
      compat.conf matching startup order; fix unbounded accumulation of
      ignore_user/ignore_group find-filter strings
[Fix] scan_stage_yara(): anchor dedup regex to prevent substring
      false-positives; per-file fallback for YARA < 4.0; stderr filter
      handles YARA-X message format; validate downloaded and compiled rules
[Fix] quarantine system: TOCTOU mv exit code check; $RANDOM replaced with
      inode naming; fix batch quarantine signature name; grep -F for literal
      matching; add missing chown in non-pub branch; fix colon truncation in
      metadata paths (.info, quarantine.hist, session.hits); issue #399
[Fix] sigignore() permanently deletes from on-disk signature files on every
      scan; moved ignore filtering into gensigs() runtime copies; signatures
      no longer irrecoverably lost between updates
[Fix] view_report() and genalert() sendmail path prepends SUBJECT: header
      into canonical session files, corrupting reports for subsequent views
[Fix] CLI robustness: 19 bare exit statements given explicit codes;
      -c/--checkout, -x/--exclude-regex, -i/--include-regex, -q/--quarantine,
      -n/--clean, -s/--restore, and --web-proxy reject missing/empty
      arguments with clear error messages; issue #366
[Fix] install.sh: man page compression on fresh install; backup robustness;
      upgrade no longer kills inotify monitoring; guard SysV registration
      with systemd check; guard chattr -ia with command -v; preserve
      hookscan config and pub/ state; issue #414
[Fix] FreeBSD detection: replace broken $OSTYPE check with cached uname -s;
      all 9 dead code paths functional; id -u (POSIX) replaces id --user;
      restore() touch -t for FreeBSD mtime restoration
[Fix] clamselector() logs warning on clamd test failure instead of silently
      switching; no longer overwrites user scan_max_filesize; remove invalid
      --fdpass from remote clamd TCP path; issue #452, #410
[Fix] cron.daily: fix flock lock leak to backgrounded scans; overlapping
      runs prevented with lockfile; fix dead code in update failure logging;
      config errors now propagate to cron; issue #373
[Fix] view_report() resolves "newest" and empty scan ID to most recent
      session; replace $EDITOR with cat for terminal output; issue #336
[Fix] tlog trim cursor unit mismatch: purge() and monitor_cycle() subtracted
      byte count from line-count cursor; replaced with mode-consistent units;
      issue #227
[Fix] find_recentopts incorrectly escaping find options; issue #440, pr#442
[Fix] ignore_file_ext, --exclude-regex, --include-regex, and ignore_paths:
      convert to bash arrays for correct find argument passing; empty -regex
      no longer causes find errors; issue #446, #438, #450, #72
[Fix] scan_ignore_user/scan_ignore_group with non-existent user/group no
      longer causes find to error out; issue #335
[Fix] replace ed dependency with tail/cat for log trimming, preserving file
      inode for inotifywait; issue #308
[Fix] importconf: 5 missing variables added, 16 hardcoded values replaced
      with variable expansion; hardcoded install path replaced with $inspath;
      issue #439
[Fix] scan_days config variable undocumented: add to conf.maldet, importconf,
      man page, and README; used by cron.daily for recent-file scan window
[Fix] genalert() digest mode: email_subj permanently mutated on repeated
      calls; missing session.monitor.current guard; add --connect-timeout
      and --max-time to Slack/Telegram curl calls
[Fix] scan_user_access_minuid: --mkpubpaths fallback default 10 to 100 to
      match internals.conf; expose variable in conf.maldet and importconf
[Fix] compat.conf: add missing quar_hits to quarantine_hits mapping;
      pre-1.5 configs silently lost quarantine_hits value
[Fix] --alert-daily/--monitor-report: add pre-check for running monitor
      process; exits with clear error message when no monitor is active
[Fix] miscellaneous: replace $RANDOM/$$ with mktemp throughout; replace
      which with command -v; replace egrep with grep -E; fix chown '.'
      separator to POSIX ':'; sed -r to sed -E for portability; quote
      critical variable expansions; fix lbreakifs() spurious backspace;
      replace hardcoded binary paths with command -v discovered variables;
      gensigs() temp file leak on repeated calls; ClamAV lstat() ERE filter
      escape; get_remote_file() scoping and error handling; lmdup() capture
      install.sh exit code; checkout() FTP double domain suffix
[Fix] CI: UAT job Docker build context set to project root with
      -f tests/Dockerfile; fixes COPY paths that require project root
[Fix] alert rendering: hit type regex /^\{[A-Z]+\}/ fails to match {MD5}
      signatures (digit not in [A-Z]); 84% of signatures produce empty
      hit_type, blank badges, and missing by-type summary entries
[Fix] alert rendering: empty quarpath produces consecutive tabs in manifest;
      bash read IFS=$'\t' collapses them, shifting hit_type into quarpath
      field; text reports show false quarantine paths for unquarantined hits
[Fix] alert rendering: JSON injection in Slack/Discord messaging templates;
      HIT_FILE and HIT_SIGNATURE exported as raw strings into JSON contexts;
      filenames with quotes, backslashes, or newlines break JSON payloads;
      add HIT_FILE_JSON/HIT_SIGNATURE_JSON escaped variants
[Fix] alert rendering: empty SUMMARY_* tokens in single-hit messaging;
      _lmd_compute_summary() skipped when total==1 but message templates
      reference {{SUMMARY_*}} unconditionally; produces garbled summary line
[Fix] restore() and restore_hitlist() return exit 0 on failure (invalid scan
      ID or nonexistent file); automated recovery scripts checking $? see false
      success; now returns exit 1 on all error paths
[Fix] compat.conf scan_hex_workers mapping silently ignored: conf.maldet sets
      scan_workers="0" as default, so the guard condition always fails; users
      setting deprecated scan_hex_workers via -co see no effect; condition
      changed to unconditionally map when scan_hex_workers is set
[Fix] local var=$(mktemp) masks exit code in _yara_scan_rules() and
      trim_log(); split into separate declaration and assignment per project
      convention
[Fix] email alert delivery fails with "No such file or directory" when
      email_format is html/both but no HTML session file exists (pre-2.0.1
      scan sessions); _resolve_html_for_session() renders HTML on demand
      from preserved hits file; falls back to text only when hits file is
      also missing; view_report() and genalert() share the same helper;
      regression tests for on-demand rendering and text fallback
[Fix] on-demand HTML rendering for older scan sessions produces empty scan
      metadata fields (scan ID, dates, path, totals); _parse_session_metadata()
      extracts metadata from the text session header before rendering
[Fix] sigup() md5 verification uses bare relative filenames; if cwd shifts
      before hash check, md5sum and awk read wrong files or fail; use absolute
      $tmpwd/ paths for all four hash operations
[Fix] _safe_source_conf() permits PATH, LD_PRELOAD, BASH_ENV, IFS and other
      dangerous environment variable overrides from remote config; values pass
      the metacharacter guard (no shell chars) but overwrite inherited env;
      add variable name blocklist before printf -v assignment
[Fix] clean() uses global $hitname instead of $file_signame parameter for
      clean rule lookup; wrong clean rule selected when global is stale or
      differs from the value passed as arg2; use $file_signame parameter

  -- Changes --

[Change] HTML email rendered on-demand at send time from current templates;
      persistent .html session files no longer stored; old scan reports
      always use the latest email design; eliminates the empty-file-path
      bug class (base64 < "") and simplifies session file management;
      _resolve_html_for_session() renders to temp file for both clean and
      dirty scans; gen_report() and genalert() digest no longer write .html
[Change] clean scan emails show celebration block: green checkmark with
      "No Threats Detected" and file count summary instead of empty stat
      blocks and orphaned "Threat Details" heading; scan header template
      refactored to use pre-rendered {{SCAN_RESULT_HTML}} token with
      separate result-clean.tpl and result-dirty.tpl sub-templates;
      {{THREAT_BADGE_HTML}} token replaces hardcoded threat badge (green
      "All Clear" for clean, red count for dirty); _lmd_compute_summary()
      handles empty manifests by setting SUMMARY_* tokens to zero
[Change] HTML email templates: responsive fluid hybrid layout with Outlook
      conditional tables (mso), progressive CSS media queries for mobile
      (480px breakpoint), and text-size-adjust for iOS/Android; summary data
      merged into header as colored stat blocks (threats/cleaned/quarantined)
      with by-type breakdown; scan, panel, and digest headers redesigned;
      HTML summary templates replaced (content now in header); render pipeline
      computes summary before header for token availability
[Change] HTML email templates widened from 600px to 700px for better
      readability of long YARA signatures and file paths
[Change] HTML entry card layout redesigned: signature name spans full width
      with counter right-aligned, type badge moved to detail row below for
      more efficient use of horizontal space
[Change] HTML summary card reflowed from cramped 4-column to 2x2 stacked
      pairs (hits/quarantined, cleaned/status) for clearer readability
[Change] HTML template label columns standardized to consistent widths
      (100px headers, 80px entry details) across scan, panel, and digest
[Change] HTML meta bar date field uses word-break for long date strings

[Change] Performance: eliminate ~500,000 fork/exec operations by replacing
      external command pipelines with Bash builtins and consolidating
      duplicated code blocks across scan, quarantine, monitor, and
      alerting paths
[Fix] Fix glob expansion bugs with adversarial filenames and
      space-splitting in unprotected paths
[Change] maldet.service EnvironmentFile changed from conf.maldet to
      /etc/sysconfig/maldet or /etc/default/maldet; ExecStart uses
      ${MONITOR_MODE:-users}
[Change] rewrite usage_short() and usage_long() with categorized sections
      and complete option coverage
[Change] maldet.1 man page rewritten following man-pages(7) conventions
[Change] README.md: add 28 missing config variables; document Discord
      alerting, YARA batch scanning, hookscan auto-detection; correct
      multiple variable descriptions
[Change] document --monitor RELOAD, --mkpubpaths, --alert-daily, and
      scan_find_timeout minimum threshold across all CLI documentation
      surfaces
[Change] internals.conf: remove 6 orphaned variables; add usermod and
      column binary discovery
[Change] vendored libraries updated: tlog_lib.sh v2.0.3, elog_lib.sh v1.0.2,
      alert_lib.sh v1.0.3, pkg_lib.sh v1.0.1
[Change] vendored libraries: batsman submodule updated to v1.2.0
[Change] batch quarantine: extract dest paths once for bulk chmod/chown/touch;
      pre-load inode map into enriched manifest to eliminate per-file awk lookups
[Change] _scan_progress(): emit plain newline-terminated output in non-TTY
      contexts (cron, pipe, docker exec); ANSI escape sequences (\033[1G,
      \033[K) now gated behind [ -t 1 ] TTY check
[Change] alert rendering: merge _lmd_render_text and _lmd_render_html into
      parameterized _lmd_render() helper; thin wrappers preserve API
[Change] install.sh: show header and copyright before any operations; organize
      output into labeled sections (backup, install, config import, signatures)
      using pkg_lib section primitives; distinguish upgrade vs fresh install;
      end with success summary matching BFD installer conventions
[Change] alert entry rendering: replace per-entry bash loop (O(N) forks) with
      single-pass awk _lmd_render_entries(); eliminates ~8 process forks per hit
      for all render paths (text, html, slack, telegram, discord); type registry
      moved into _lmd_parse_hitlist awk BEGIN block (6-field enriched manifest);
      html/json escaping computed in awk; removes _lmd_set_entry_vars,
      _lmd_hit_type_color, _lmd_hit_type_label (dead code after refactor)
